1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,840
=Episode 12=

3
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:01,840
Zinuo,

4
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,799
come on, give me a hand.

5
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:08,479
Dad, what's this?

6
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,960
It's a present I got for you.

7
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:12,879
Really?

8
00:02:13,879 --> 00:02:14,960
Really, of course.

9
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:16,680
Thanks, Dad.

10
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:19,560
(2013)
Dad,

11
00:02:19,759 --> 00:02:20,800
(2013)
why is this so heavy?

12
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:22,680
Because there's

13
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,080
a little cuckoo inside.

14
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:25,919
A cuckoo?

15
00:02:26,039 --> 00:02:26,479
Yeah.

16
00:02:26,879 --> 00:02:27,800
Soon we'll let it

17
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,360
fly out.

18
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:29,680
Yay!

19
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:31,479
Let's go.

20
00:02:37,759 --> 00:02:38,360
Tasty, huh?

21
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,080
Slow down, don't choke.

22
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,960
Let me get you some water.

23
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,080
Mom.

24
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:15,680
Go on up.

25
00:03:22,719 --> 00:03:23,520
How much weight did you gain?

26
00:03:29,319 --> 00:03:30,039
0.2 kg.

27
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:39,840
What are you doing?

28
00:03:40,439 --> 00:03:41,000
Get away.

29
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:11,800
You don't take this seriously.

30
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,040
Only three days till the competition.

31
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:19,759
Go

32
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:20,800
practice the piano.

33
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:42,759
Hello.

34
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,319
Hello, who are you looking for?

35
00:04:45,959 --> 00:04:46,480
And you are?

36
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:47,759
I'm the security

37
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:48,439
captain here.

38
00:04:54,710 --> 00:04:56,420
(Zhan Chun, Security Captain)

39
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,360
Zhan Chun?

40
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,600
It used to be Dadong.

41
00:05:02,839 --> 00:05:03,240
Yeah.

42
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,920
Dadong left. He's sick.

43
00:05:05,399 --> 00:05:05,839
Lung disease.

44
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:08,439
You know Dadong?

45
00:05:09,319 --> 00:05:10,079
I used to live here.

46
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:13,000
This place? It's already sold.

47
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:13,959
I know.

48
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,839
I still have some things

49
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,199
inside.

50
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:23,000
Can't be. This place has changed
hands several times.

51
00:05:23,399 --> 00:05:24,240
There's nothing left inside.

52
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:24,879
Everything's been ripped out.

53
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:27,199
How do you know

54
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:28,319
there's nothing inside?

55
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,839
Just... just some construction debris.

56
00:05:35,879 --> 00:05:36,920
You went inside?

57
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:39,439
I haven't been inside. I...

58
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:40,680
How could I possibly get in?

59
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:41,199
I didn't.

60
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,360
You want the stuff inside too?

61
00:05:44,399 --> 00:05:45,000
I don't want it.

62
00:05:45,639 --> 00:05:46,199
I don't.

63
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:23,319
Someone still has his eye
on 505's money.

64
00:06:23,639 --> 00:06:24,279
Who?

65
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:26,839
The security captain here,

66
00:06:27,399 --> 00:06:28,160
Zhan Chun.

67
00:07:28,759 --> 00:07:29,279
Wenwen.

68
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,480
I'm sorry.

69
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:32,839
No need to say sorry.

70
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,120
I mean it.

71
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,480
Sorry means sorry.

72
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,399
My dad shouldn't have done that.

73
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:37,240
at the school gate the other day.

74
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,480
I got angry at him.

75
00:07:38,759 --> 00:07:39,639
And my mom scolded him.

76
00:07:43,319 --> 00:07:44,040
You're not throwing it away?

77
00:07:48,399 --> 00:07:49,079
I realized

78
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,319
if it weren't for my dad,

79
00:07:50,639 --> 00:07:51,560
I wouldn't have all those socks.

80
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:52,720
I'm really sorry.

81
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:53,839
I'll talk to him too.

82
00:07:54,199 --> 00:07:55,319
What does it have to do with you?

83
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:56,560
We are us.

84
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,639
Your dad is your dad.

85
00:07:57,759 --> 00:07:58,560
My dad is my dad.

86
00:08:01,279 --> 00:08:01,879
Cool or what?

87
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,240
Totally cool.

88
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,160
Dashing, huh?

89
00:08:15,279 --> 00:08:15,959
Sun Lanying!

90
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,279
The crazy woman is here.

91
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:21,000
We don't want to be like her.

92
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,240
We must be good girls.

93
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,079
You too, okay?

94
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:25,720
Come on.

95
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,279
Eat up, don't be picky.

96
00:08:27,519 --> 00:08:29,120
Lay nice eggs for Wenwen.

97
00:08:29,959 --> 00:08:30,639
Sun Lanying.

98
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,720
Look at what your son Yu Ming

99
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:32,559
has done.

100
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:33,919
Done what?

101
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,720
Look at you, rushing around.

102
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,039
Are you trying to start trouble again?

103
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:39,039
Give me the money.

104
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:41,159
Give back Qian Weijie's money

105
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,000
right now.

106
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,480
What?

107
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,559
Slow down, slow down.

108
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:48,519
Slow down.

109
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:52,399
I'll do it.

110
00:08:55,919 --> 00:08:57,080
You can't see it.

111
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,240
Does it hurt?

112
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:01,639
I'm fine.

113
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:02,559
Ma'am,

114
00:09:02,799 --> 00:09:03,600
I'm sorry.

115
00:09:04,039 --> 00:09:05,600
I was supposed to take care of you.

116
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,720
Now you're taking care of me.

117
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:09,080
Don't say that.

118
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,240
How could your man

119
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:12,399
hit you so hard?

120
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:14,840
What did he hit you with?

121
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,240
A wine bottle?

122
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,840
Once he's drunk,

123
00:09:18,159 --> 00:09:19,440
he doesn't know his own strength.

124
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,559
It's nothing.

125
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,159
People say

126
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,759
that never stand

127
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:28,279
between a man and his wife.

128
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:29,519
But in your situation,

129
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:31,440
if you don't leave him,
what will you do?

130
00:09:34,039 --> 00:09:35,039
My daughter is still little.

131
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,039
I don't want her to grow up
without a father.

132
00:09:37,799 --> 00:09:39,120
That makes sense.

133
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,600
Once you have a child,

134
00:09:40,639 --> 00:09:41,759
it's not easy to divorce.

135
00:09:44,159 --> 00:09:45,840
A while back, Yitong

136
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,279
almost got divorced too.

137
00:09:48,559 --> 00:09:50,559
Partly for Wenwen's sake,

138
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,559
and also...

139
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:56,639
What?

140
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:58,720
It's young people's business.

141
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,120
I can't really explain.

142
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:03,399
Something went wrong
in their relationship.

143
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:05,080
It's fine now. It's in the past.

144
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,000
All resolved.

145
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,399
Good that it's resolved then.

146
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,799
I see Yu doesn't come home often.

147
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:14,039
He's very busy with work?

148
00:10:14,279 --> 00:10:15,120
Him?

149
00:10:15,519 --> 00:10:17,600
He's just a drifter.

150
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,759
What's he busy with?

151
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:20,159
He runs a cultural creative shop.

152
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:21,320
Business isn't good.

153
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,919
A shop like that can do well, though.

154
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,639
Why is business bad?

155
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,279
Where is his shop?

156
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:30,559
I don't know. I've never been there.

157
00:10:31,679 --> 00:10:33,039
Tong says it's very far.

158
00:10:33,559 --> 00:10:35,399
Seems like it's in some tourist area.

159
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:40,240
Don't get it wet.

160
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:41,080
Okay.

161
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,240
Let me carry it.

162
00:10:43,039 --> 00:10:44,480
Your back still hasn't healed.

163
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:45,360
Let's go.

164
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:45,799
I've got it.

165
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:47,080
Don't worry about me.

166
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:47,720
Just hurry up.

167
00:10:47,879 --> 00:10:48,360
Careful.

168
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:52,120
Child, you have a hard life.

169
00:10:52,639 --> 00:10:53,720
Such a hard life.

170
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:54,600
It's nothing.

171
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,279
Forgot the mirror.

172
00:10:58,960 --> 00:10:59,720
Slow down.

173
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,120
They have another foothold.

174
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,600
Should be in some tourist area.

175
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,120
Do you know how many

176
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,440
tourist areas there are in Luzhou?

177
00:11:17,759 --> 00:11:18,759
Which tourist area exactly?

178
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,080
Fan Meijuan doesn't know either.

179
00:11:20,519 --> 00:11:21,840
I'll try to dig for more info.

180
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,279
Keep a close eye on them.

181
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,320
Gotta go.

182
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,159
Dad, my phone died yesterday.

183
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,120
It was off. I didn't see it. Sorry.

184
00:12:05,399 --> 00:12:05,879
Look.

185
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:08,279
This is the agreement with the bank.

186
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,559
Four copies in total.

187
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:12,039
Your Ming signed right here.

188
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:13,039
I'm telling you,

189
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,840
Yu Ming is committing fraud.

190
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:16,440
Don't you go around telling lies.

191
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,120
He blushes

192
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,080
every time he tells a lie.

193
00:12:19,399 --> 00:12:20,639
Him? Commit fraud? Ridiculous.

194
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:21,320
Lanying,

195
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,039
you don't know

196
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,679
Ming's abilities these days.

197
00:12:23,919 --> 00:12:24,879
He's great at sucking up.

198
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:25,799
Right now,

199
00:12:25,879 --> 00:12:27,480
he treats money
as if it were his own parents.

200
00:12:27,879 --> 00:12:28,480
You know that?

201
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,440
He's always talking about 130 million.

202
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,480
130 million.

203
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,480
I'm telling you,

204
00:12:32,559 --> 00:12:33,440
this kind of greed

205
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:34,879
will turn a heart black.

206
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,440
It's not just me

207
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,559
calling him a fraudster.

208
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:38,559
He really is a fraud.

209
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,480
Now the bank is accusing him of fraud.

210
00:12:40,519 --> 00:12:41,240
You know that?

211
00:12:41,279 --> 00:12:43,320
Have you lost your mind?

212
00:12:43,399 --> 00:12:44,360
Sun Lanying,

213
00:12:44,399 --> 00:12:45,360
the bank

214
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:47,360
is suing him now.

215
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,879
If it weren't for the deep

216
00:12:48,919 --> 00:12:50,799
sisterly bond between us...

217
00:12:50,919 --> 00:12:51,440
Oh, that's right,

218
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,679
I must be out of my mind.

219
00:12:52,759 --> 00:12:54,360
I came all the way here to warn you

220
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:55,000
myself.

221
00:12:55,159 --> 00:12:56,000
Right now, Ming is about

222
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,159
to be arrested and locked up.

223
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,919
I never should have let Weijie

224
00:12:58,919 --> 00:13:00,200
get involved in this.

225
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:02,440
Now he's completely disgraced,

226
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,480
and he's furious.

227
00:13:03,519 --> 00:13:04,440
I should've

228
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:05,960
listened to Qian Lai and just stayed

229
00:13:06,279 --> 00:13:07,120
out of it.

230
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:15,600
(Yu Ming)

231
00:13:19,510 --> 00:13:20,700
(Yu Ming)

232
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,360
What now?

233
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,000
You recognize his handwriting, right?

234
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:31,080
Are you saying Weijie can manage this?

235
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:32,679
Why should he manage it?

236
00:13:37,279 --> 00:13:37,919
Tong.

237
00:13:38,879 --> 00:13:39,360
Gentlemen,

238
00:13:39,519 --> 00:13:41,000
come, come, take a seat.

239
00:13:41,279 --> 00:13:42,120
Two bowls of satay noodles

240
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,480
and a platter of braised meat.

241
00:13:44,679 --> 00:13:45,159
Sounds good?

242
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,960
It's on the house today.

243
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:47,639
Okay?

244
00:13:47,799 --> 00:13:48,639
Thank you, thank you.

245
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,039
Dad.

246
00:13:55,039 --> 00:13:56,000
Do you still remember

247
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:56,919
that song I wrote

248
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,039
when I was little?

249
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,159
The lyrics

250
00:13:59,159 --> 00:14:01,639
sounded a lot like a love song.

251
00:14:02,159 --> 00:14:03,000
Mr. Money.

252
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:04,919
I know.

253
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,440
It was pretty well written.

254
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,600
I wrote

255
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,039
that song for money.

256
00:14:10,759 --> 00:14:12,480
When I was young,

257
00:14:13,279 --> 00:14:14,440
I was a bit brash.

258
00:14:14,919 --> 00:14:15,840
Angry at the world.

259
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:19,000
Back then, I didn't like money,

260
00:14:19,399 --> 00:14:21,480
but I was afraid that
one day, I'd need it badly.

261
00:14:22,639 --> 00:14:23,919
That's pretty much what it meant.

262
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:26,480
And I turned out to be right.

263
00:14:28,039 --> 00:14:28,799
Now,

264
00:14:30,039 --> 00:14:30,960
the older you get,

265
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,080
the more you realize
how important money is.

266
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,919
I really once believed

267
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,840
money could solve everything.

268
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:41,879
You were thinking too shallowly.

269
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:43,000
Yeah.

270
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,200
Now I know.

271
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,039
Since my brother was gone,

272
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:50,200
I've had this hole in my heart.

273
00:14:51,799 --> 00:14:52,720
It lets the wind in.

274
00:14:53,879 --> 00:14:55,960
I've tried everything to plug it up.

275
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,519
But after many years,

276
00:14:58,519 --> 00:14:59,519
it still hasn't been plugged.

277
00:15:01,039 --> 00:15:03,679
I thought money could plug it.

278
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:06,679
But now I know

279
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,679
it doesn't work that way.

280
00:15:09,679 --> 00:15:10,720
The suffering you're meant to endure,

281
00:15:11,399 --> 00:15:12,200
you still have to endure.

282
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:14,159
If you can't settle down,

283
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,519
then you just can't settle down.

284
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:18,360
The lottery ticket...

285
00:15:18,519 --> 00:15:19,600
Did you win

286
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,600
or not?

287
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,399
Here's another 2,000.

288
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:53,000
No need to count it.

289
00:15:53,879 --> 00:15:54,600
Alright, alright.

290
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,240
Qian Weijie

291
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:02,720
asked me to bring you a message.

292
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,000
He says,

293
00:16:04,159 --> 00:16:07,320
big mouth, thick skin, but no skill
means nothing.

294
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:11,919
A blockhead is always a blockhead.

295
00:16:12,679 --> 00:16:13,639
Little ability?

296
00:16:14,039 --> 00:16:15,600
Then keep your temper good.

297
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,360
If you don't have the skills,

298
00:16:17,519 --> 00:16:18,879
don't try to fake it.

299
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,240
If he alone

300
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:21,559
wants to embarrass himself,
so be it.

301
00:16:21,759 --> 00:16:22,919
But don't turn our whole family

302
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,440
into a laughingstock.

303
00:16:24,879 --> 00:16:26,279
It was Qian Weijie

304
00:16:26,279 --> 00:16:27,279
who paid willingly.

305
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:28,840
I didn't take a single bite.

306
00:16:28,879 --> 00:16:29,480
Lanying,

307
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:30,879
when you ask someone for help,

308
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:33,159
you need the right attitude.

309
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,919
♪Work hard and make money♪

310
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:48,360
♪I want to get rich♪

311
00:16:49,399 --> 00:16:50,200
Mom's calling.

312
00:16:52,159 --> 00:16:52,639
Mom.

313
00:16:52,919 --> 00:16:54,000
Come over here right now.

314
00:16:54,279 --> 00:16:55,639
Put everything else aside.

315
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:56,840
Come now.

316
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,000
Mom wants me to come over.

317
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,120
She sounds really angry.

318
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,679
Coming.

319
00:17:05,279 --> 00:17:05,920
Where is he?

320
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,079
Young people have so much going on.

321
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:14,680
Well...

322
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:15,920
Try it.

323
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:19,880
Decades later,

324
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:20,440
same taste.

325
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:23,720
It'd be trouble if it weren't.

326
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,119
You're back.

327
00:17:47,319 --> 00:17:48,079
Mom.

328
00:17:50,559 --> 00:17:51,079
You're just like

329
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,799
worthless mud
that won't stick to a wall.

330
00:17:53,160 --> 00:17:54,160
That's you exactly.

331
00:17:54,559 --> 00:17:55,759
I've worked so hard

332
00:17:55,759 --> 00:17:56,759
raising you up.

333
00:17:56,799 --> 00:17:57,400
And for what?

334
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:58,759
You can't do one proper thing.

335
00:17:58,799 --> 00:18:00,920
Every day, you mess around
with useless stuff.

336
00:18:01,119 --> 00:18:02,359
Seriously, you think

337
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,279
you can achieve something big?

338
00:18:04,359 --> 00:18:05,599
Think you're something special?

339
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:08,000
One meal, and you can spend 37,000.

340
00:18:08,119 --> 00:18:09,240
I must have

341
00:18:09,279 --> 00:18:10,839
committed some great sin

342
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,519
in my past life.

343
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,720
How else could I

344
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,319
have such a useless child like you?

345
00:18:15,759 --> 00:18:16,200
You used to

346
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,240
be just like

347
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:17,920
your father.

348
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,839
Never proper.

349
00:18:19,359 --> 00:18:20,160
And now?

350
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,559
Now, you even cheat your own family.

351
00:18:22,359 --> 00:18:23,880
If you were half as good as Feng,

352
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,200
I'd be thanking God.

353
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,799
Stop bringing up Yu Feng, Mom.

354
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,079
Yu Feng's dead!

355
00:18:28,119 --> 00:18:29,000
He's gone!

356
00:18:29,119 --> 00:18:30,039
He's not here anymore!

357
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,200
Only I'm left!

358
00:18:31,759 --> 00:18:33,400
I'm begging you, look at me!

359
00:18:33,559 --> 00:18:34,839
Look at this house!

360
00:18:35,079 --> 00:18:36,720
It's all photos of Yu Feng.

361
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,680
All Yu Feng's awards.

362
00:18:38,799 --> 00:18:40,440
Am I not your biological son?

363
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:41,839
Was I adopted or something?

364
00:18:42,119 --> 00:18:43,799
I've already tried so hard.

365
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,759
I can't help it, Mom.

366
00:18:46,079 --> 00:18:47,839
I want to be outstanding

367
00:18:47,839 --> 00:18:48,839
like my brother too.

368
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,559
Just like you,

369
00:18:50,839 --> 00:18:52,319
God wouldn't see me.

370
00:18:52,759 --> 00:18:53,920
What am I supposed to do?

371
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:56,880
I could just die.

372
00:18:57,519 --> 00:18:59,119
I'd make a deal with the Reaper.

373
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:01,200
I'll never be reincarnated

374
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,559
in exchange for Yu Feng's next life,

375
00:19:02,799 --> 00:19:03,960
so he can be your son again.

376
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:04,759
How about that?

377
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,559
You used to

378
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:21,400
listen to this piece all the time.

379
00:20:22,039 --> 00:20:23,799
You could say
it was your musical awakening.

380
00:20:30,039 --> 00:20:31,440
This song, up till now,

381
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,920
is your best one, I think.

382
00:20:33,559 --> 00:20:34,920
If you made an album,
it'd definitely sell.

383
00:20:36,119 --> 00:20:36,799
Before,

384
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:37,799
that guy, Hong Jinkui,

385
00:20:37,799 --> 00:20:39,200
said he had connections.

386
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:41,039
So I gave him the money.

387
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,000
Then he scammed me.

388
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:45,680
Tell me,

389
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:47,359
how much more do you need?

390
00:20:48,119 --> 00:20:48,920
About...

391
00:20:51,319 --> 00:20:52,160
80,000 yuan.

392
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,720
Come on, hurry up, go.

393
00:20:54,319 --> 00:20:55,440
Go to your sister-in-law's place.

394
00:20:55,799 --> 00:20:56,519
Borrow some from her.

395
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,839
It's not your fault.

396
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,640
At least you survived.

397
00:21:58,519 --> 00:22:00,680
That's our blessing in misfortune.

398
00:22:06,039 --> 00:22:07,079
Your mom

399
00:22:08,039 --> 00:22:09,000
has an extreme personality.

400
00:22:10,279 --> 00:22:11,799
But she's a very simple person.

401
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,599
She just wants to firmly

402
00:22:14,599 --> 00:22:15,599
hold this family together

403
00:22:16,480 --> 00:22:17,720
and live a steady life.

404
00:22:19,559 --> 00:22:20,480
Music,

405
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:21,839
to her,

406
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:23,200
is too distant.

407
00:22:23,839 --> 00:22:24,759
Too vague.

408
00:22:28,279 --> 00:22:30,319
It's true she gave more affection

409
00:22:33,279 --> 00:22:34,359
to your brother.

410
00:22:35,559 --> 00:22:37,160
Because from him, she could see

411
00:22:37,160 --> 00:22:38,039
more certainty

412
00:22:38,039 --> 00:22:40,200
than either you or I ever had.

413
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,319
Your mom hides her feelings very deep.

414
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,079
So deep that sometimes

415
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,279
she herself forgets.

416
00:22:48,279 --> 00:22:49,720
But you should know

417
00:22:51,279 --> 00:22:52,519
she loves you.

418
00:23:08,759 --> 00:23:10,079
Beaten like that and still not

419
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:11,160
calling the police?

420
00:23:11,319 --> 00:23:12,200
What is she thinking?

421
00:23:12,359 --> 00:23:13,519
It's all for the child.

422
00:23:13,799 --> 00:23:14,920
If the man is locked up,

423
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,119
it affects the kid's future.

424
00:23:17,640 --> 00:23:18,519
Dinner's ready.

425
00:23:19,519 --> 00:23:20,599
Wenwen, come out and eat.

426
00:23:22,079 --> 00:23:22,720
There's one more soup.

427
00:23:22,759 --> 00:23:23,480
I'll go get it.

428
00:23:23,839 --> 00:23:24,279
Okay.

429
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,000
Coming.

430
00:23:33,559 --> 00:23:34,160
Jiang Juan,

431
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:36,680
well, about your family matter,

432
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,279
it's not really

433
00:23:37,279 --> 00:23:38,559
our place to interfere.

434
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:40,880
But seeing how badly you're hurt

435
00:23:41,039 --> 00:23:42,079
and you're still working,

436
00:23:42,079 --> 00:23:43,480
it makes us feel bad.

437
00:23:44,039 --> 00:23:45,319
Maybe you should take a few days off.

438
00:23:45,319 --> 00:23:46,079
Once your injuries heal,

439
00:23:46,079 --> 00:23:47,759
you can come back and look after my mom.

440
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,759
It's nothing.

441
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:51,599
Just some surface wounds.

442
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,839
I'm used to it.

443
00:23:53,119 --> 00:23:53,960
I have no idea

444
00:23:54,079 --> 00:23:55,960
how he managed to find me.

445
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,279
But I can't

446
00:23:57,279 --> 00:23:58,400
go back to that place.

447
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,640
I plan to find another place.

448
00:24:01,119 --> 00:24:01,960
Then just stay here.

449
00:24:02,839 --> 00:24:03,759
It'll be safer.

450
00:24:04,359 --> 00:24:04,920
Stay.

451
00:24:06,559 --> 00:24:07,440
I'm going to do my homework.

452
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,599
She hasn't eaten yet.

453
00:24:11,079 --> 00:24:12,240
She's always liked strong flavors.

454
00:24:12,279 --> 00:24:13,119
She probably thinks

455
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:13,960
it's a bit too bland.

456
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:14,759
It's okay. We'll order her

457
00:24:14,759 --> 00:24:15,680
some fried chicken later.

458
00:24:15,839 --> 00:24:16,680
Let me go check on her.

459
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:17,480
You stay put.

460
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:18,400
Your back is in such bad shape.

461
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,400
Stop walking around.

462
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:19,960
Careful, careful.

463
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:20,599
I'll take a look.

464
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:22,799
If she won't eat, it's fine.

465
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:24,599
Who knows

466
00:24:24,599 --> 00:24:26,079
if that fried chicken is safe to eat?

467
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,480
I'll mix her a dipping sauce.

468
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,640
With this tofu pudding in it,

469
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:29,359
it'll be so good.

470
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:30,079
It'll just take a moment.

471
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,400
Too bland? You can't get used to it?

472
00:24:34,759 --> 00:24:35,920
Are you feeling unwell?

473
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:38,559
Sick?

474
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:41,039
You're not sick.

475
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:42,720
What's the matter?

476
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,279
How can there be people this evil?

477
00:24:45,319 --> 00:24:46,759
Beating Ms. Jiang like that.

478
00:24:47,359 --> 00:24:48,920
I want to help, but I can't.

479
00:24:49,119 --> 00:24:51,039
There's this anger stuck in my chest.

480
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:52,559
I can't swallow it.

481
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:53,920
Ms. Jiang is usually

482
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:54,720
so nice to me.

483
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,519
I really feel sorry for her.

484
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,880
You're just too kind-hearted.

485
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:00,559
Can't stand seeing people suffer.

486
00:25:01,359 --> 00:25:02,759
She's a pitiful person.

487
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:05,119
Her man bullies her.

488
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,519
Now he's beaten her again.

489
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:07,720
She has a daughter

490
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:08,960
about your age.

491
00:25:09,279 --> 00:25:10,640
With her out here making a living,

492
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,279
they never get to see each other.

493
00:25:13,799 --> 00:25:16,480
It's a very complicated world.

494
00:25:16,559 --> 00:25:18,000
Not all bad people

495
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,400
get punished.

496
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,599
There's not much we can do for her.

497
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,680
If you want to help her,

498
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,039
just treat her well.

499
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:26,160
Understand?

500
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:30,480
I get it.

501
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,000
What's wrong?

502
00:25:48,039 --> 00:25:48,799
It's nothing.

503
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:51,240
Oh, it's bad luck.

504
00:25:51,799 --> 00:25:52,720
Yao is fine.

505
00:25:53,039 --> 00:25:53,640
It's fine.

506
00:25:54,599 --> 00:25:55,119
It's nothing.

507
00:26:01,079 --> 00:26:02,279
It's all okay.

508
00:26:03,599 --> 00:26:04,319
Just eat.

509
00:26:05,079 --> 00:26:06,400
It'll get cold if you don't eat.
Come on.

510
00:26:15,079 --> 00:26:16,440
Won't you be hungry later
if you don't eat?

511
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,440
I made you a chili oil dip.

512
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,559
Spicy and fragrant.

513
00:26:19,759 --> 00:26:20,799
Mix it with the tofu.

514
00:26:20,839 --> 00:26:21,599
It's the absolute best.

515
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:22,440
Try some.

516
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:28,839
Tasty.

517
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,000
If it's tasty, eat more.

518
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:31,839
No fried chicken tonight, okay?

519
00:26:33,039 --> 00:26:33,960
Fried chicken isn't healthy.

520
00:26:37,780 --> 00:26:40,250
(Bridgeway Financial)

521
00:26:40,319 --> 00:26:41,279
This security guard

522
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,160
used to be Hu Deshuai's driver.

523
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:45,920
Hu Deshuai trusted him.

524
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,039
A lot of sensitive,
profit-related matters

525
00:26:48,079 --> 00:26:49,039
were handled by him.

526
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:52,559
He has a lover named Jiang Juan.

527
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:55,400
Right now, she's at Yu Ming's house,

528
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:56,519
looking after his mother-in-law.

529
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,119
Jiang Juan

530
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:00,160
used to work as a nanny

531
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:00,880
in Hu Deshuai's home.

532
00:27:01,559 --> 00:27:02,839
Took care of his paralyzed father

533
00:27:02,839 --> 00:27:03,960
for five years.

534
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:06,599
After Hu Deshuai died,

535
00:27:07,079 --> 00:27:08,480
the two of them left Luzhou.

536
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:09,720
(Du Lei)
They just got back.

537
00:27:10,359 --> 00:27:11,799
(Du Lei)
These two are kind of interesting.

538
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,480
Hu Deshuai was likely

539
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:15,039
killed by the two of them together.

540
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:19,200
Get the truth out of him.

541
00:27:25,759 --> 00:27:26,720
You want to

542
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:29,279
squeeze that money out of that couple,

543
00:27:29,599 --> 00:27:30,920
and you even push your own woman

544
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,440
out front as an undercover agent.

545
00:27:33,279 --> 00:27:35,519
You've got quite
a few tricks up your sleeve.

546
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:38,319
Did you two

547
00:27:39,079 --> 00:27:40,480
kill Hu Deshuai?

548
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,400
Yes, it was me.

549
00:27:54,039 --> 00:27:54,680
I did it.

550
00:27:55,079 --> 00:27:55,640
Why?

551
00:27:55,799 --> 00:27:57,079
I wanted the money he hid.

552
00:27:57,279 --> 00:27:57,960
I wanted it.

553
00:27:58,160 --> 00:27:58,839
How much did he hide?

554
00:27:59,039 --> 00:27:59,880
He hid 30 million.

555
00:28:00,039 --> 00:28:00,559
30 million.

556
00:28:00,839 --> 00:28:01,880
Hidden in the villa?

557
00:28:02,319 --> 00:28:03,759
Yes, yes.

558
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:09,440
Does this money have anything to do
with you?

559
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,680
There's something fishy
about this money.

560
00:28:16,799 --> 00:28:18,519
Get him out of there first.
He's in the way.

561
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,640
No! It has nothing to do with me!

562
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:23,480
Nothing.

563
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,880
You have one week

564
00:28:26,319 --> 00:28:27,319
to leave Luzhou.

565
00:28:27,559 --> 00:28:28,480
And never come back.

566
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:29,200
Can you do that?

567
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:29,880
I can do it.

568
00:28:30,039 --> 00:28:30,720
I hear you.

569
00:28:31,039 --> 00:28:31,720
I can do it.

570
00:29:10,039 --> 00:29:10,599
Hungry?

571
00:29:20,519 --> 00:29:21,400
Here, eat up.

572
00:29:23,799 --> 00:29:24,640
Don't be afraid, eat.

573
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,519
We're the same.

574
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:27,279
Chained up, right?

575
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,079
Eat up.

576
00:29:32,119 --> 00:29:32,759
Looking down on me?

577
00:29:35,119 --> 00:29:36,119
You look down on me, don't you?

578
00:29:36,319 --> 00:29:36,759
Just eat.

579
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,720
I'm living worse than a dog.

580
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:09,440
Miss,

581
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:10,759
who are you looking for?

582
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,799
I'm looking for Mr. Yu.

583
00:30:13,599 --> 00:30:15,680
At this hour? He should be
in the old performance hall.

584
00:30:16,079 --> 00:30:16,640
That one.

585
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:18,559
Go to the performance building lobby,

586
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,079
turn right, all the way to the end.

587
00:30:20,599 --> 00:30:21,160
Thanks.

588
00:31:33,799 --> 00:31:34,839
My performance of this piece...

589
00:31:35,799 --> 00:31:36,680
Even today,

590
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,640
I still haven't surpassed Pei.

591
00:31:41,279 --> 00:31:42,759
Your instrument isn't fixed yet.

592
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,319
Come back in a few days to pick it up.

593
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:01,519
Mr. Yu,

594
00:32:03,119 --> 00:32:04,240
I came to see you today

595
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:07,000
because you are Yu Shiyi.

596
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:09,839
When I was in Germany,

597
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,079
Pei spent the most time

598
00:32:12,079 --> 00:32:12,880
with me.

599
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:15,000
Besides practicing the piano,
she gave me

600
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,119
all of her time.

601
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:18,640
She told me about a man.

602
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,039
About his talent,

603
00:32:22,400 --> 00:32:23,240
about his insecurity,

604
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,200
about his suffocating marriage

605
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,200
that crushed him so he couldn't breathe.

606
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:31,720
About how unfair fate

607
00:32:32,359 --> 00:32:33,279
made him unable to recover.

608
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:35,960
But even so,

609
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:38,160
his light still shone brightly.

610
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:42,680
I believe I'm not

611
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,880
standing here without reason.

612
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:46,960
I'm just here to tell you,

613
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:48,839
Pei said

614
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:50,880
she won't see you anymore.

615
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:53,119
She wishes you well.

616
00:33:15,020 --> 00:33:19,240
(1993)

617
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,480
Last week,
we rehearsed "Jacqueline's Tears."

618
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,680
Piano and cello...

619
00:33:24,039 --> 00:33:25,400
Their tones are clearly so fitting,

620
00:33:26,119 --> 00:33:27,799
yet always separated by a movement.

621
00:33:29,039 --> 00:33:30,519
Only able to echo each other

622
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:33,400
in different pitches,
different time-spaces.

623
00:33:35,559 --> 00:33:36,160
I don't want to be

624
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:37,599
the cello part that's forever chasing.

625
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:48,799
The charm of polyphony

626
00:33:49,039 --> 00:33:51,119
lies in each independent voice,

627
00:33:51,319 --> 00:33:53,480
never truly being able to overlap.

628
00:33:55,039 --> 00:33:55,640
I'm sorry.

629
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:17,800
I see you,

630
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:18,639
Huang Xiaoping.

631
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:19,599
Come here.

632
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:22,079
It's Jiang Xiaoling, Mr. Hong.

633
00:34:22,159 --> 00:34:23,199
A couple of years ago,

634
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:25,199
we couldn't catch a glimpse of you.

635
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:26,960
Now, you come five times a week.

636
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:28,280
Don't give me that crap.

637
00:34:29,079 --> 00:34:30,400
Last time, didn't I come here

638
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:31,480
and enter the password myself

639
00:34:31,519 --> 00:34:32,920
to pay
Unit 505's property management fees?

640
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:33,559
They were all here,

641
00:34:33,559 --> 00:34:34,039
all witnesses.

642
00:34:34,079 --> 00:34:34,760
Listen,

643
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:36,280
right now,

644
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:37,440
Unit 505's current owner, Yu Ming, and I

645
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:38,719
have a financial dispute.

646
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:39,920
According to the Civil Code,

647
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:40,519
I have the right

648
00:34:40,519 --> 00:34:41,239
to get this 120,000 back.

649
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:41,719
Refund it for me.

650
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:43,159
This money has already been booked.

651
00:34:43,239 --> 00:34:44,960
And last time you paid,

652
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:46,000
we didn't put

653
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,239
any pressure on you.

654
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:48,760
The surveillance cameras recorded it.

655
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:49,800
Besides, your financial dispute

656
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,199
with Mr. Yu?

657
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:52,400
You two sort it out yourselves.

658
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,199
Don't give me

659
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:53,920
all that nonsense.

660
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:54,440
And don't try to scare me

661
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,559
with your security footage crap.

662
00:34:55,559 --> 00:34:56,480
Just give me a straight answer.

663
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:57,679
Are you refunding the money today
or not?

664
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:58,599
If you don't refund it,

665
00:34:58,679 --> 00:34:59,559
I'll immediately call

666
00:34:59,559 --> 00:35:00,760
your higher regulatory department.

667
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:01,840
And I'll file a complaint

668
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:02,559
with the consumer association.

669
00:35:02,639 --> 00:35:03,760
Then I'll find the media

670
00:35:03,840 --> 00:35:04,679
and expose you.

671
00:35:04,719 --> 00:35:05,719
So? Refund or not?

672
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:07,719
Mr. Hong,

673
00:35:08,519 --> 00:35:10,000
please take out your phone.

674
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:14,599
Wouldn't it have been easier
if you'd taken this attitude earlier?

675
00:35:16,239 --> 00:35:17,480
I didn't want to make it hard
for you guys either.

676
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:18,000
Right?

677
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:19,320
Come on then.

678
00:35:20,199 --> 00:35:20,840
Refund it to my WeChat.

679
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:23,719
Please go ahead and call

680
00:35:23,719 --> 00:35:25,079
the regulatory department right now.

681
00:35:50,079 --> 00:35:51,480
I've finally got you cornered.

682
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:53,000
Go ahead, run. Try to run.

683
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:53,639
What's this?

684
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:54,599
Listen up, Yu Ming,

685
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:56,119
this is pure and simple fraud.

686
00:35:56,360 --> 00:35:57,199
When did I commit fraud?

687
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:57,800
Don't play dumb

688
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,119
with me here.

689
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,320
You pocketed that 1.02 million.

690
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,719
You're pretty comfortable
with that, huh?

691
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:02,480
If I hadn't been told

692
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:03,280
you didn't win the lottery,

693
00:36:03,280 --> 00:36:04,400
I'd still be dreaming at home.

694
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:05,880
Did I ever say I won the lottery?

695
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:06,679
Did I say it with my own mouth?

696
00:36:06,679 --> 00:36:08,440
It was all your own imagination.

697
00:36:08,519 --> 00:36:09,360
Don't you push me,

698
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:09,840
I'm telling you.

699
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:10,639
You pushed me first.

700
00:36:10,639 --> 00:36:11,599
Yu Ming, answer me this.

701
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:12,639
In this house of yours,

702
00:36:12,639 --> 00:36:13,639
is there 30 million hidden?

703
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,599
Is there?

704
00:36:15,559 --> 00:36:16,599
What are you talking about?

705
00:36:16,639 --> 00:36:17,320
One minute it's 130 million,

706
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:18,119
next it's 30 million.

707
00:36:18,119 --> 00:36:18,960
Can't you have any judgment

708
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:19,719
of your own?

709
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:20,639
This house is mine.

710
00:36:20,679 --> 00:36:21,800
Don't you think I know

711
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:23,039
how much money is inside?

712
00:36:23,079 --> 00:36:24,039
This house is yours?

713
00:36:24,079 --> 00:36:24,679
Of course it's mine.

714
00:36:24,679 --> 00:36:25,000
What are you saying?

715
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,599
How can you be so shameless?

716
00:36:26,639 --> 00:36:27,639
You're the shameless one here.

717
00:36:27,679 --> 00:36:28,639
I paid off that

718
00:36:28,639 --> 00:36:29,440
900,000 in loan sharks for you,

719
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:30,639
plus 120,000
in property management fees.

720
00:36:30,639 --> 00:36:31,440
Give it all back to me.

721
00:36:31,519 --> 00:36:32,440
And the stuff in this house

722
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:33,360
should be split with me too.

723
00:36:33,679 --> 00:36:34,599
Why should it go to you?

724
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:35,920
We signed a contract.

725
00:36:36,039 --> 00:36:37,400
Everything inside here belongs to me.

726
00:36:37,519 --> 00:36:38,400
It's all clearly written.

727
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:39,280
Have you forgotten?

728
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:40,280
All yours?

729
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:40,800
What now?

730
00:36:41,719 --> 00:36:42,599
You gonna hit me now?

731
00:36:42,639 --> 00:36:43,519
Are you hitting me?

732
00:36:57,119 --> 00:36:57,599
What's the matter?

733
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:58,840
Mr. Yu,

734
00:36:59,559 --> 00:37:00,679
you saved my life.

735
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:01,960
I could die for you.

736
00:37:16,719 --> 00:37:17,559
Let's talk another day.

737
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:27,079
Thank you.

738
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:28,280
Thank you.

739
00:37:28,519 --> 00:37:29,079
Mr. Yu,

740
00:37:29,719 --> 00:37:30,840
my body is fine now,

741
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:31,639
full of energy.

742
00:37:33,079 --> 00:37:33,840
I can even jump.

743
00:37:34,039 --> 00:37:34,760
Good health is what matters.

744
00:37:35,159 --> 00:37:36,400
Once that two million is sorted out,

745
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,559
I'll definitely return it intact.

746
00:37:37,599 --> 00:37:37,880
Okay.

747
00:37:37,880 --> 00:37:38,760
But the most important thing right now

748
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:40,079
is that we fill this hole quickly.

749
00:37:40,079 --> 00:37:41,079
- Alright? Come on.
- Okay.

750
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:42,840
Come on, follow me.

751
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,039
Make way.

752
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:54,960
I'm burning up.

753
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:56,599
The last couple of days
weren't this stifling.

754
00:38:02,239 --> 00:38:02,840
I'm so thirsty.

755
00:38:03,039 --> 00:38:03,480
Bro.

756
00:38:04,039 --> 00:38:04,719
Wait here.

757
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:06,199
I'll go up and ask for some water.

758
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:06,920
No, no, no.

759
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:08,000
Don't take advantage
of everything.

760
00:38:08,519 --> 00:38:08,960
San.

761
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:10,159
Buy us some water.

762
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:11,239
Sure.

763
00:38:12,199 --> 00:38:12,719
And...

764
00:38:13,639 --> 00:38:14,480
Get some snacks too.

765
00:38:15,639 --> 00:38:16,119
Okay.

766
00:38:16,679 --> 00:38:17,440
You guys keep working.

767
00:38:20,119 --> 00:38:20,760
Take a break.

768
00:38:21,519 --> 00:38:22,199
Sit down for a bit.

769
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:25,360
Yu Ming, you scum.

770
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:26,719
You just rely on having

771
00:38:26,719 --> 00:38:27,280
more helpers.

772
00:38:27,639 --> 00:38:28,760
Just wait till the day you're alone.

773
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:29,719
I'll kill you.

774
00:38:30,559 --> 00:38:31,119
Sorry.

775
00:38:55,079 --> 00:38:55,559
How much?

776
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:56,480
22 yuan.

777
00:38:56,679 --> 00:38:57,159
QR code payment?

778
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:46,199
How did this guy get in?

779
00:41:46,679 --> 00:41:48,719
How could he know about this hole?

780
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:53,559
Did he follow me here?

781
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:52,000
Take a break.

782
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:52,960
Have some water, guys.

783
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,159
I bought you something to eat.

784
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,880
(Next Episode)

785
00:43:08,199 --> 00:43:09,320
(Actress, Ren Suxi)
I'm Ren Suxi.

786
00:43:09,480 --> 00:43:11,400
(Actress, Ren Suxi)
I invite you to watch Wonder Wall.

787
00:43:11,800 --> 00:43:12,800
Help!

788
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:13,880
Save my dad!

789
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:15,639
Save my son first!

790
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:16,840
Slowly.

791
00:43:16,960 --> 00:43:17,480
Dad!

792
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:19,320
You're an adult.

793
00:43:19,480 --> 00:43:20,480
Can you act like one?

794
00:43:20,599 --> 00:43:22,199
Stop making everyone worry about you.

795
00:43:22,920 --> 00:43:23,800
Let's turn ourselves in.

796
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:25,559
Ask a lawyer about the sentence.

797
00:43:25,719 --> 00:43:26,639
Based on past cases,

798
00:43:26,639 --> 00:43:27,360
at least ten years.

799
00:43:28,639 --> 00:43:29,000
Yu Ming!

800
00:43:29,199 --> 00:43:29,679
Yu Ming!

801
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:31,039
Why not just give him

802
00:43:31,039 --> 00:43:31,840
the 1.02 million?

803
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:32,920
That's not

804
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:34,079
what he wants.

805
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:36,360
He wants the 60 million.

806
00:43:36,760 --> 00:43:37,440
Yu Ming!

807
00:43:55,610 --> 00:44:02,620
♪The road ahead is still so long
Where have you gone?♪

808
00:44:04,180 --> 00:44:11,340
♪Under the blazing sun
I keep heading north♪

809
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:20,220
♪To those who pass me by
You don't have to look at me♪

810
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:28,640
♪Just keep walking your own way
I'll manage on my own♪

811
00:44:31,630 --> 00:44:35,230
♪Is the rain falling hard?♪

812
00:44:35,870 --> 00:44:39,000
♪Is there someone
to hold an umbrella for you?♪

813
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:44,940
♪The wind has blown
the numbers off the signs♪

814
00:44:44,940 --> 00:44:47,930
♪Where am I supposed to go?♪

815
00:44:48,730 --> 00:44:52,250
♪Can I change my mind?♪

816
00:44:53,010 --> 00:44:56,240
♪How do I go on without you?♪

817
00:44:57,550 --> 00:45:02,080
♪When will this
endless rain finally stop?♪

818
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:04,780
♪Then I'll wait for you♪

819
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:08,780
♪Please don't leave me waiting♪

820
00:45:23,060 --> 00:45:26,590
♪Is the rain falling hard?♪

821
00:45:27,410 --> 00:45:30,750
♪Is there someone
to hold an umbrella for you?♪

822
00:45:31,610 --> 00:45:36,450
♪The wind has blown
the numbers off the signs♪

823
00:45:36,450 --> 00:45:39,730
♪Where am I supposed to go?♪

824
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:44,130
♪Can I change my mind?♪

825
00:45:44,490 --> 00:45:47,800
♪How do I go on without you?♪

826
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:53,430
♪When will this
endless rain finally stop?♪

827
00:45:53,430 --> 00:45:56,190
♪Then I'll wait for you♪

828
00:45:56,190 --> 00:46:00,040
♪Please don't leave me waiting♪
